      "correct": 0,
      "difficulty": "facil",
      "hints": [
        "Es una de las derivadas fundamentales",
        "La derivada de sin(x) es cos(x)",
        "Memoriza: d/dx[sin(x)] = cos(x)"
      ],
      "stepByStep": [
        "📚 **Derivada del seno**",
        "",
        "**Fórmula fundamental:**",
        "$$\\frac{d}{dx}[\\sin(x)] = \\cos(x)$$",
        "",
        "💡 **Demostración (por límite)**",
        "",
        "$$\\frac{d}{dx}[\\sin(x)] = \\lim_{h \\to 0} \\frac{\\sin(x+h) - \\sin(x)}{h}$$",
        "",
        "Usando identidades trigonométricas:",
        "$$= \\lim_{h \\to 0} \\frac{\\sin(x)\\cos(h) + \\cos(x)\\sin(h) - \\sin(x)}{h}$$",
        "",
        "$$= \\sin(x) \\lim_{h \\to 0} \\frac{\\cos(h) - 1}{h} + \\cos(x) \\lim_{h \\to 0} \\frac{\\sin(h)}{h}$$",
        "",
        "Como $\\lim_{h \\to 0} \\frac{\\cos(h) - 1}{h} = 0$ y $\\lim_{h \\to 0} \\frac{\\sin(h)}{h} = 1$:",
        "",
        "$$= \\sin(x) \\cdot 0 + \\cos(x) \\cdot 1 = \\cos(x)$$",
        "",
        "✅ **Respuesta**",
        "$\\frac{d}{dx}[\\sin(x)] = \\cos(x)$"
      ],
      "explanation": "La derivada de sin(x) es cos(x), una fórmula fundamental del cálculo"
    },
